summary: Taylor Swift's "1989 (Taylor's Version)" is her fourth album remake, released in 2023. It's a synth-pop album inspired by the 1980s, featuring 21 songs, including five new ones. The album was well-received by critics for its production, Swift's vocals, and the new tracks. It topped charts in many countries and had seven songs in the Billboard Hot 100 top 10. This album is part of Swift's project to re-record her old music due to a dispute over ownership.
title: 1989 (Taylor's Version)
